ence Lab.', 70034, 0), (451561, 'The PATRIOT Act brought down the wall separating intelligence agencies from law enforcement and other entities charged with protecting the Nation from terrorism.', 66641, 0), (451562, 'Legislation passed in the aftermath of September 11, 2001 enhanced our intelligence capabilities and strengthened our national defense, but until now our nation''s immigration policies have not adapted to the needs of a post-September 11th world.', 66641, 0), (451563, 'Intelligence, if it is clever in the direction of the better, is responsible for the greatest benefits of all.', 31012, 0), (451564, 'How does nature amplify the intelligence of groups? It forms swarms.', 70105, 0), (451565, 'I had been involved in U.S. intelligence in Berlin, Germany, while in the military and had worked with a contact with the Central Intelligence Agency office there.', 70325, 0), (451566, 'We focus on a unique form of artificial intelligence called artificial swarm intelligence.', 70105, 0), (451567, 'Beyond individual intelligence, nature has also cultivated intelligence through swarms. For example, bees, birds and fish act in a more intelligent way when acting together as a swarm, flock or school.', 70105, 0), (451568, 'We developed a technology called artificial swarm intelligence, which is all about tapping the inherent knowledge, wisdom, intuition of groups.', 70105, 0), (451569, 'When a species wants to tap the collective intelligence of a population, they don''t take a poll; they don''t take a vote. They form a real-time system.', 70105, 0), (451570, 'Swarm intelligence is like a brain of brains.', 70105, 0), (451571, 'The long-term value of amplifying the intelligence of people is a lot more important than betting on sports.', 70105, 0), (451572, 'Prince Charles is an absolute Mountbatten. The real intelligence in the royal family comes through my parents to Prince Philip and the children.', 72168, 0), (451573, 'I strongly support the call to greatly expand our human intelligence capability to penetrate al Qaeda and gather critical intelligence to prevent terrorist attacks on our homeland.', 67378, 0), (451574, 'Our intelligence community needs better coordination of operations and exchange of information, and that''s why we need an overall director of national intelligence and a national counterterrorism center.', 67378, 0), (451575, 'People have an image of Italians. When I go somewhere in the world, I don''t care where it is, when they look at me it''s not about my intelligence. It''s who can I beat up.', 72169, 0), (451576, 'We''ve done it in intelligence sharing and certain elements of security. There were parts of the department, in fact, that worked very well in Katrina, like the Coast Guard and TSA.', 72170, 0), (451577, 'Look, people have an image of Italians. When I go somewhere in the world, I don''t care where it is, when they look at me it''s not about my intelligence. It''s who can I beat up.', 72169, 0), (451578, 'The qualities I am looking for in Miss Right are intelligence and humour.', 68590, 0), (451579, '''Emma'' is my favorite Jane Austen novel - one of my favorite novels period; a novel about intelligence outsmarting itself, about a complicated, nuanced, irresistible heroine who does everything wrong.', 34382, 0), (451580, 'We have no regulation of drones in the United States in their commercial use. You can see drones some day hovering over the homes of Hollywood luminaries, violating privacy. This question has to be addressed. And we need rules of operation on the border, by police, by commercial use, and also by military and intelligence use.', 33473, 0), (451581, 'George Tenet has been the director of central intelligence since 1997, time enough to have changed the Agency''s culture. He has failed. He should go.', 72171, 0), (451582, 'The heartbeat of a football team is the quarterback position and I think everyone who has any intelligence about the game understands you must have consistency at 